@rem --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Description "Description"
Generate log-file entries in PhoneLog standard (SGML) format.
Similar to AmiLog, can be used with AmiTCP/IP.

@endnode

@rem --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Requirements "Requirements"
- If you want to use the installer-script you need AmiTCP/IP 4.3
@endnode

@rem --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Installation "Installation/Usage"
- For use with AmiTCP/IP 4.3 use the installer script.
- For use with other software:

  PLogStart HOSTNUMBER/A/K,HOSTNAME/K,REASON/K,LOGFILE/K

  PLogEnd LOGFILE/K

  where

  HOSTNUMBER - Phone number of the host you are connected too
  HOSTNAME   - Name of the host you are connected too (optional)
  REASON     - Reason for the call - may be 'email poll' (optional)
  LOGFILE    - Log-file to write too. Default: 'AmiTCP:log/PLog.log'

  Every PLogStart must be followed by a PLogEnd, or the format of the log file is broken!
@endnode

@rem --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node History "History"
27.01.1996 -	First release
03.04.1996 -	Second release (Installer-script update for AmiTCP/IP 4.3)
04.04.1996 -	Third release (Bug fixed Installer-script :(
@endnode

@rem --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@node Bugs "Known bugs"
- If you break AmiTCP 4.2 or below while it tries to connect a host then the PLogEnd will be called. This results in a broekn log file! This can be fixed by using a text editor and removing the wrong end of the log entry.

- If your machine crashes during a AmiTCP connection, the last log entry is still open, because PLogEnd was not called. This can be fixed by removing the start of the entry, or better by completing the entry by hand.
@endnode

